definitions.definition: a position in an organization, such as the army, showing the importance of the person having it:
a particular position, higher or lower than others:
examples: He's in the front/first rank of (= one of the best) international tennis players.

definitions.definition: the members of a group or organization:
examples: Party ranks have swelled by nearly 300,000.

definitions.definition: to be moved up from a low level position in an organization to a higher one:
examples: He rose through the ranks to become a general.

definitions.definition: (especially of something bad) complete or extreme:
examples: It was rank stupidity to drive so fast on an icy road.

definitions.definition: to have a position higher or lower than others, or to be considered to have such a position:
examples: A captain ranks (= has a position) above a lieutenant.
